<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1048] Lock.obtain(timeout) behaves incorrectly for large timeouts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1048</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Because timeout is a long, but internal values derived from timeout&lt;br/&gt;
are ints, its possible to overflow those internal values into negative&lt;br/&gt;
numbers and cause incorrect behavior.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Spinoff from this thread:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.gossamer-threads.com/lists/lucene/java-user/54376&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.gossamer-threads.com/lists/lucene/java-user/54376&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
